---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Changelog">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900">Changelog</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-500 leading-relaxed">Product updates, new features, and improvements.</p>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-12">
      <article>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <time class="text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600">April 2026</time>
          <span class="rounded-full bg-indigo-50 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-indigo-700 ring-1 ring-indigo-100">Latest</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">API Security Hardening</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>Broken Object Level Authorization fix</strong> &mdash; API key revocation now verifies org ownership to prevent cross-tenant access</li>
          <li><strong>JWT token type enforcement</strong> &mdash; Refresh tokens can no longer be used as access tokens (issuer claim validation)</li>
          <li><strong>User data minimization</strong> &mdash; Login and register responses no longer expose sensitive fields like password hash or internal flags</li>
          <li><strong>API key expiration</strong> &mdash; Optional <code>expires_in_days</code> parameter on key creation; expired keys rejected at evaluation time</li>
          <li><strong>Rate limit headers</strong> &mdash; <code>X-RateLimit-Limit</code>, <code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code>, and <code>X-RateLimit-Reset</code> on all rate-limited responses</li>
          <li><strong>Content-Type enforcement</strong> &mdash; POST/PUT/PATCH requests must use <code>application/json</code> (415 otherwise)</li>
          <li><strong>Content-Security-Policy header</strong> &mdash; Added <code>default-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'</code> to all responses</li>
          <li><strong>SSRF protection</strong> &mdash; Webhook URLs block private IPs, localhost, and internal hostnames</li>
          <li><strong>Bulk evaluation limit</strong> &mdash; <code>flag_keys</code> array capped at 100 items</li>
          <li><strong>PII masking in logs</strong> &mdash; Emails, tokens, and phone numbers are masked in server logs</li>
          <li><strong>Security audit logging</strong> &mdash; <code>api_key.created</code>, <code>api_key.revoked</code> actions tracked in audit trail</li>
          <li><strong>JWT secret startup check</strong> &mdash; Server refuses to start with default secret in non-debug environments</li>
          <li><strong>Database SSL enforcement</strong> &mdash; Default connection string now requires <code>sslmode=require</code></li>
          <li><strong>SSE CORS fix</strong> &mdash; Removed hardcoded <code>Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *</code> from SSE server</li>
          <li><strong>Request ID in errors</strong> &mdash; Error responses include <code>request_id</code> for correlation</li>
          <li><strong>Comprehensive test suite</strong> &mdash; 50+ new tests covering auth flows, middleware, org isolation, and security boundaries</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <time class="text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600">Phase 3 &mdash; April 2026</time>
        </div>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Scale &amp; Differentiation</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>A/B Experimentation</strong> &mdash; New <code>ab</code> flag type with weighted variants, consistent hashing assignment, and impression tracking API</li>
          <li><strong>Relay Proxy</strong> &mdash; Lightweight Go binary for edge caching with SSE or polling sync</li>
          <li><strong>Mutual Exclusion Groups</strong> &mdash; Prevent experiment interference with deterministic winner selection</li>
          <li><strong>Evaluation Metrics</strong> &mdash; In-memory counters, dashboard visualization with top-flags chart and reason breakdown</li>
          <li><strong>Dashboard: Eval Metrics page</strong> &mdash; Per-environment counts, reason distribution, top evaluated flags</li>
          <li><strong>Dashboard: Mutex group editor</strong> &mdash; Inline editor in flag detail with group member count</li>
          <li><strong>Stale Flag Scanner</strong> &mdash; CLI tool to find unused flag references in code, CI mode with exit code</li>
          <li><strong>Documentation Site</strong> &mdash; 35+ page Docusaurus site covering getting started, concepts, SDKs, API reference, and deployment</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article>
        <time class="text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600">Phase 2 &mdash; March 2026</time>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Enterprise Readiness</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>Python SDK</strong> &mdash; Client with polling/SSE, OpenFeature provider</li>
          <li><strong>Java SDK</strong> &mdash; Maven project with polling/SSE, OpenFeature provider, JUnit 5 tests</li>
          <li><strong>Approval Workflows</strong> &mdash; Request-review flow for production changes with automatic application</li>
          <li><strong>Webhook Dispatch</strong> &mdash; Background dispatcher with HMAC-SHA256 signatures, exponential retry, delivery logging</li>
          <li><strong>Flag Scheduling</strong> &mdash; Auto-enable/disable at specified times with 30-second granularity</li>
          <li><strong>Kill Switch</strong> &mdash; Emergency flag disable with one-click dashboard button</li>
          <li><strong>Flag Promotion</strong> &mdash; Copy flag configuration between environments</li>
          <li><strong>Flag Health Dashboard</strong> &mdash; Health scores, stale flags, expiring flags, missing descriptions</li>
          <li><strong>Prerequisite Flags</strong> &mdash; Recursive dependency evaluation</li>
          <li><strong>RBAC</strong> &mdash; Owner/admin/developer/viewer roles with per-environment permissions</li>
          <li><strong>Audit Logging</strong> &mdash; Tamper-evident log with before/after state diffs</li>
          <li><strong>CI/CD Pipeline</strong> &mdash; GitHub Actions for all SDK tests, server tests, dashboard build, Docker build</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article>
        <time class="text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600">Phase 1 &mdash; February 2026</time>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Core Platform (MVP)</h2>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-600 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>Evaluation Engine</strong> &mdash; Targeting rules, segments, percentage rollout with MurmurHash3</li>
          <li><strong>Management API</strong> &mdash; Full CRUD for projects, environments, flags, segments, API keys</li>
          <li><strong>SSE Streaming</strong> &mdash; Real-time flag updates via PostgreSQL LISTEN/NOTIFY</li>
          <li><strong>Go SDK</strong> &mdash; Polling, SSE, local eval, OpenFeature provider</li>
          <li><strong>Node.js SDK</strong> &mdash; Polling, SSE, local eval, OpenFeature provider</li>
          <li><strong>React SDK</strong> &mdash; Provider component, hooks (useFlag, useFlags, useReady, useError)</li>
          <li><strong>Dashboard</strong> &mdash; Next.js with flag management, targeting editor, segments, environments</li>
          <li><strong>Docker Compose</strong> &mdash; One-command local development setup</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
